title: On the ground: Marching with the #FeesMustFall protesters
text:
Today saw the ninth day of the nationwide #FeesMustFall student protest, in which students are demanding no increase in university fees.
Protest action in Johannesburg started off a little directionless, but soon turned into a calculated and deliberate march to hand over a memorandum of demands to the ANC at Luthuli House.
There's alot of fervour but no real plan of action yet. Students waiting to make next move #jhbshutdown pic.twitter.com/KUlYDc8HYG
— Grethe Koen (@GretheKoen) October 22, 2015 Wits students and those in solidarity with the #FeesMustFall movement gathered in the streets around the university’s campus at around 10am, where they were met by students from the University of Johannesburg who had marched from their campus.
